<grammar>
<section>
<title>Past simple: &lt;i&gt;was&lt;/i&gt; and &lt;i&gt;were: &lt;/i&gt;positive and negative forms</title>
<sectiontitle>The past of &lt;i&gt;be&lt;/i&gt; is &lt;i&gt;was/were&lt;/i&gt;. We use &lt;i&gt;I/he/she/it was&lt;/i&gt; and &lt;i&gt;you/we/they were.&lt;/i&gt;</sectiontitle>
<titlesound>el_gram_7_1_1.mp3</titlesound>
<text1>I'm at home today.</text1>
<text1a>&lt;b&gt;I was&lt;/b&gt; at home yesterday.</text1a>
<sound1>el_gram_7_1_2.mp3</sound1>
<text2>We're very cold.</text2>
<text2a>&lt;b&gt;We were&lt;/b&gt; very cold.  </text2a>
<sound2>el_gram_7_1_3.mp3</sound2>
<sectiontitle2>In the negative, we use &lt;i&gt;I/he/she/it was not&lt;/i&gt; and &lt;i&gt;you/we/they were not. &lt;/i&gt;We usually use the short forms&lt;i&gt;, wasn't&lt;/i&gt; and &lt;i&gt;weren't.&lt;/i&gt;</sectiontitle2>
<titlesound2>el_gram_7_1_4.mp3</titlesound2>
<text3>She was not at school.</text3>
<text3a>&lt;b&gt;She wasn't&lt;/b&gt; at school.</text3a>
<sound3>el_gram_7_1_5.mp3</sound3>
<text4>They were not very comfortable.</text4>
<text4a>&lt;b&gt;They weren't&lt;/b&gt; very comfortable.</text4a>
<sound4>el_gram_7_1_6.mp3</sound4>
</section>
<section>
<title>Past simple: &lt;i&gt;was&lt;/i&gt; and &lt;i&gt;were: &lt;/i&gt;question form </title>
<sectiontitle>In the question, we use &lt;i&gt;was I/he/she/it &lt;/i&gt;and&lt;i&gt; were you/we/they&lt;/i&gt;. </sectiontitle>
<titlesound>el_gram_7_1_7.mp3</titlesound>
<text1>It was good.</text1>
<text1a>&lt;b&gt;Was it&lt;/b&gt; good? Yes, it was.</text1a>
<sound1>el_gram_7_1_8.mp3</sound1>
<text2>They weren't at work.</text2>
<text2a>&lt;b&gt;Were they&lt;/b&gt; at work? No, they weren't.</text2a>
<sound2>el_gram_7_1_9.mp3</sound2>
